ounts of how religion is experienced differently across social groups to better understand the role that religion plays in the lives of Americans today and how that is changing.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Mai 2021) 0aReligion and politicszUnited States. 0aReligion and sociologyzUnited States. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Sociology of Religion.2bisacsh  aaccessible.  aamerican religious beliefs and behaviors.  abirth.  adeath.  ademographic data.  ademographic processes.  aeducation.  aemployment.  aengaging.  aeveryday accounts of religion.  afamilies.  agender.  amigration.  aprayer.  arace and ethnicity.  areligious affiliation.  areligious practices and beliefs.  arole of religion in america.  aservice attendance.  asocial class.1 aChipman Gilliland, Claire, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDTL Humanities 2020z978311073776908iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020 Englishz978311070471608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020z9783110704518oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Social Sciences 2020 Englishz978311070472308iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Sociology, Education, Psychology 2020z9783110704549oZDB-23-SEW08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUC Press Frontlist eBook-Package 2020z978311069041540uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/9780520968929zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de Gruyter40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520968929423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780520968929.jpg  a978-3-11-069041-5  UC Press Frontlist eBook-Package 2020b2020  a978-3-11-070471-6  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020 Englishb2020  a978-3-11-070472-3  EBOOK PA